WEBVTT

00:02.270 --> 00:03.737
I'm Carin -- with a "C."

00:03.771 --> 00:05.139
We need to be friends.
[ Glasses clink ]

00:05.173 --> 00:07.308
What you really want
is revenge on the FBI.

00:07.341 --> 00:09.910
You raid that money
before the FBI does.

00:09.943 --> 00:11.745
We'll do
all the work for you.

00:11.779 --> 00:14.782
[ Shouting in Spanish ]

00:22.190 --> 00:25.025
I'm gonna pick up Jacob, and
then you want to steal $50,000.

00:25.059 --> 00:26.594
We don't have a choice.

00:26.627 --> 00:28.996
Suddenly you have a rich
grandmother I never heard of.

00:29.029 --> 00:29.997
So?

00:30.030 --> 00:31.865
-How much?
-$50,000.

00:31.899 --> 00:34.402
You're getting to be
a very good player.

00:34.435 --> 00:35.769
You're pretty good, too.

00:35.803 --> 00:37.471
[ Gun cocks ]
Ow!

00:38.806 --> 00:40.808
[ Gunshot ]
Aah!

00:42.643 --> 00:45.213
[ Door closes, lock clicks ]

00:57.158 --> 01:00.228
[ Lowered voice ] You let all
the wrong people stay alive.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.463
[ Lowered voice ]
I should have killed him...

01:02.496 --> 01:04.998
in front of Jacob?

01:10.304 --> 01:14.775
[ Sighs, scoffs ]

01:14.808 --> 01:17.178
This was a mistake.

01:18.612 --> 01:20.448
From day one.

01:25.519 --> 01:30.090
**

01:30.124 --> 01:31.825
[ Lights click off ]

01:36.797 --> 01:38.599
[ Door unlocks ]

01:38.632 --> 01:41.935
Shit. [ Sighs ]

01:41.969 --> 01:44.272
I thought you were a bad guy.

01:52.546 --> 01:54.748
So...

01:54.782 --> 01:56.284
it's the middle of the night.

01:56.317 --> 01:59.820
I guess sometimes you just
need to talk to your mom,

01:59.853 --> 02:01.622
no matter what time it is.

02:01.655 --> 02:04.858
So I'm your mom again?

02:06.627 --> 02:07.861
You betrayed me.

02:07.895 --> 02:10.698
I didn't betray you.
I protected you.

02:10.731 --> 02:12.600
At least I tried to.

02:12.633 --> 02:14.868
Nice try.

02:19.573 --> 02:21.709
I knew what I was doing.

02:21.742 --> 02:23.644
We had rules.

02:23.677 --> 02:26.046
You think making rules means
they're gonna get followed?

02:26.079 --> 02:28.349
What magazine
you read that in?

02:28.382 --> 02:30.551
Look, I'm not --

02:32.753 --> 02:34.822
I'm not here to --

02:38.091 --> 02:40.561
I need to ask you
for something.

02:45.599 --> 02:48.101
Jacob should be with you.

02:49.437 --> 02:53.507
**

02:53.541 --> 02:55.175
[ Exhales ]

02:59.947 --> 03:01.915
-[ Crying ]
-Don't worry.

03:01.949 --> 03:05.853
[ Sobs ]
I barely touched his room.

03:05.886 --> 03:07.187
[ Sniffling ]

03:07.221 --> 03:08.989
Rob put an exercise bike
in there,

03:09.022 --> 03:12.393
but we can wheel it out,
no problem.

03:21.569 --> 03:24.538
I keep picturing
this life in my head...
Mm-hmm.

03:24.572 --> 03:27.941
...you know, where the three
of us are this happy family,

03:27.975 --> 03:31.612
and it just...never works.

03:32.813 --> 03:35.949
"The three of us"?

03:35.983 --> 03:38.952
Javier is in the car
with Jacob.

03:38.986 --> 03:44.558
**

03:44.592 --> 03:46.960
So you found a loophole
for your hit man.

03:46.994 --> 03:48.929
He's not --

03:48.962 --> 03:51.465
Look, we all do bad things.

03:53.967 --> 03:55.969
Mom. Mom.

03:56.003 --> 03:58.205
It's not Javier over Jacob.

03:58.238 --> 04:01.275
I shouldn't be
with either of them.

04:01.309 --> 04:04.077
I shouldn't be with anybody.

04:06.314 --> 04:09.517
I'll have Rob go move
the exercise bike.

04:13.787 --> 04:19.159
**

04:19.192 --> 04:20.994
All right, come on.
[ Dog barks ]

04:21.028 --> 04:22.663
Come on.

04:22.696 --> 04:25.032
Come on. Get in. Get in.

04:28.135 --> 04:30.170
Go to your mom.

04:36.209 --> 04:39.447
Jacob, sit here. Sit down.

04:45.118 --> 04:48.722
I want only good things
for you, Jacob.

04:50.891 --> 04:53.193
And I want you to be safe.

04:53.226 --> 04:55.696
Especially safe.

04:55.729 --> 04:58.966
I love you too much to let
anything bad happen to you

04:58.999 --> 05:01.101
ever again.

05:01.134 --> 05:03.371
I know.

05:03.404 --> 05:07.675
So it's probably better for me
here...just childhood-wise.

05:09.810 --> 05:11.679
Right.

05:15.416 --> 05:17.451
Jacob:
But I had fun with you.

05:17.485 --> 05:19.720
Yeah.

05:19.753 --> 05:22.490
I had fun with you, too.

05:22.523 --> 05:24.692
And we'll have fun again
one day.

05:29.430 --> 05:32.633
Not tomorrow.

05:32.666 --> 05:35.068
[ Voice breaking ]
No, not tomorrow.

05:41.442 --> 05:42.810
[ Crying ]

05:42.843 --> 05:45.112
You'll have fun with Fred.

05:47.881 --> 05:50.484
[ Crying, sniffling ]

05:50.518 --> 05:53.454
Thanks for getting him
for me.

05:55.856 --> 05:58.692
Make sure to feed him.

05:58.726 --> 06:00.428
I will.

06:17.645 --> 06:20.113
Come on, Jacob.

06:23.984 --> 06:25.886
[ Sniffles ]

06:25.919 --> 06:27.755
I love you, baby.

06:27.788 --> 06:29.723
I know.

06:29.757 --> 06:31.459
I love you, too.

06:31.492 --> 06:41.469
**

06:41.502 --> 06:48.041
**

06:48.075 --> 06:54.882
**

06:54.915 --> 06:57.485
* Hard time forgiving

06:57.518 --> 07:00.120
* Even harder forgetting

07:00.153 --> 07:02.255
* Before you do something

07:02.289 --> 07:04.892
* You might regret, friend

07:04.925 --> 07:07.495
* Bricks are caving in

07:07.528 --> 07:09.897
* Oh, how sweet this sin

07:09.930 --> 07:12.500
* I left you the keys

07:12.533 --> 07:14.835
* You won't let me in

07:14.868 --> 07:17.270
* Hard time forgiving

07:17.304 --> 07:20.007
* Even harder forgetting

07:20.040 --> 07:22.309
* Before you do something

07:22.342 --> 07:25.913
* You might regret, friend

07:25.946 --> 07:29.483
Celebrate! Good times!
Come on!

07:29.517 --> 07:31.819
[ Cork pops ]
Whoo! [ Laughs ]

07:31.852 --> 07:33.521
Where's Christian?

07:33.554 --> 07:36.990
He's taking a night class
at The Learning Annex.

07:37.024 --> 07:39.827
I'm already considering
annulment.

07:42.530 --> 07:45.265
What's wrong with you two?

07:45.298 --> 07:46.634
Nothing.
[ Glass thuds ]

07:46.667 --> 07:49.202
-Can we go?
-Pump the brakes, sweetheart.

07:49.236 --> 07:51.805
Gotta make sure it's all there.

07:51.839 --> 07:54.842
-It's all there. I counted it.
-Yeah, so did I.

07:54.875 --> 07:57.310
As if I'm gonna trust
Bonnie and Clyde.

07:57.344 --> 07:59.312
Gonna count every dollar,

07:59.346 --> 08:02.282
and if there's a penny
less than 500 grand --

08:02.315 --> 08:05.385
You'll what?
Make us rob another drag club?

08:05.418 --> 08:08.388
ChantÃ©, you stay.

08:13.326 --> 08:15.362
One hundred...

08:21.268 --> 08:25.405
I think my vision gets
really bad when I'm with you.

08:25.438 --> 08:28.676
Worse than it already is.

08:28.709 --> 08:31.278
Yours does, too.

08:32.946 --> 08:35.749
It gets down to this little
point where all we can see

08:35.783 --> 08:38.085
is each other.

08:38.118 --> 08:41.622
And it feels really good to have
someone look at you like that.

08:44.925 --> 08:51.198
But it means we can't actually
see anything else around us...

08:51.231 --> 08:53.701
or anyone around us.

08:56.469 --> 09:00.440
We do all this damage,
and we don't care or notice

09:00.473 --> 09:02.342
because it's in our...

09:02.375 --> 09:04.444
**

09:04.477 --> 09:06.379
...what do you call it?

09:06.413 --> 09:10.017
Peripheral.

09:10.050 --> 09:11.652
Yeah.

09:16.089 --> 09:21.394
* How much time is there?

09:21.428 --> 09:24.564
* Before the sun is gone

09:24.598 --> 09:28.468
* And our hearts are banned
-Want anything?

09:28.501 --> 09:31.571
* Crying in our palms

09:31.605 --> 09:35.475
* And I put my white flag
in the wind *

09:35.508 --> 09:39.647
* And I feel it
in the underflow *

09:39.680 --> 09:43.083
**

09:43.116 --> 09:47.054
* I feel it in the underflow

09:47.087 --> 09:50.557
**

09:50.590 --> 09:54.594
* I feel it in the underflow

09:57.330 --> 10:01.434
* And we miss each other
in the dark *

10:01.468 --> 10:04.938
* Like ships in the night

10:04.972 --> 10:07.507
* And I cried a puddle

10:07.540 --> 10:12.079
* Deep into the valley
of shoulder blades *

10:12.112 --> 10:16.116
* And I breathe smoke
into the sky *

10:16.149 --> 10:19.419
* To let love know
I'm getting high *

10:19.452 --> 10:24.491
* There'll be no rest tonight

10:29.296 --> 10:30.931
**

10:30.964 --> 10:33.767
Woman on recording:
Today, I feel good.

10:33.801 --> 10:36.369
I am glad to be alive.

10:36.403 --> 10:39.272
I live by my positive choices.

10:39.306 --> 10:41.942
* Ba-ba-ba-ba-ba-ba!

10:41.975 --> 10:45.445
**

10:45.478 --> 10:47.715
* I trust my heart to you

10:47.748 --> 10:50.884
**

10:50.918 --> 10:53.053
* I trust my heart to you

10:54.922 --> 10:56.356
Nate.

10:57.424 --> 10:58.859
San Pellegrino with lime?

10:58.892 --> 11:01.729
Still your drink?
Still my drink.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.498
Let me get you a napkin.

11:05.532 --> 11:15.508
**

11:15.542 --> 11:18.979
* I-I-I swear my heart...

11:19.012 --> 11:21.849
**

11:21.882 --> 11:23.984
Man: Thanks for calling
the Resort at Blue Crest.

11:24.017 --> 11:26.920
How may I direct your call?
Room 613, please.

11:26.954 --> 11:28.188
[ Line rings ]

11:28.221 --> 11:30.924
[ Beep ]

11:30.958 --> 11:36.163
**

11:36.196 --> 11:37.564
[ Elevator bell dings ]

11:37.597 --> 11:39.199
724, please.

11:39.232 --> 11:42.102
[ Phone rings ]

11:42.135 --> 11:43.771
**

11:43.804 --> 11:47.775
* I am on my good behavior

11:47.808 --> 11:54.882
**

11:54.915 --> 11:57.417
[ Knock on door ]

11:58.551 --> 12:01.021
Man: Ms. Beaumont?

12:01.054 --> 12:03.757
Ms. Beaumont, your office sent
some papers for you to sign.

12:05.926 --> 12:08.896
[ Souther accent ] Just slide
them under the door, please.

12:22.910 --> 12:27.915
**

12:27.948 --> 12:30.383
1121, please.

12:30.417 --> 12:31.919
[ Phone rings ]

12:31.952 --> 12:33.386
[ Beep ]

12:33.420 --> 12:38.391
**

12:38.425 --> 12:39.893
[ Beeping, lock clicks ]

12:39.927 --> 12:43.596
**

12:45.933 --> 12:55.909
**

12:55.943 --> 13:05.118
**

13:07.955 --> 13:17.697
**

13:17.730 --> 13:19.432
[ Lighter clicks ]

13:19.466 --> 13:29.442
**

13:29.476 --> 13:31.811
**

13:31.845 --> 13:33.881
[ Exhales deeply ]

13:33.914 --> 13:43.891
**

13:43.924 --> 13:51.031
**

13:51.064 --> 13:54.034
[ Audience laughing on TV ]

13:54.067 --> 14:04.044
**

14:04.077 --> 14:14.054
**

14:14.087 --> 14:18.025
**

14:18.058 --> 14:19.592
Hey.

14:21.461 --> 14:23.997
You're at home?

14:24.031 --> 14:26.033
You alone?

14:27.400 --> 14:28.902
[ Chewing ]

14:28.936 --> 14:32.572
[ Utensil clattering ]

14:34.207 --> 14:36.676
I forgot how good
Cap'n Crunch is.

14:36.709 --> 14:38.678
Uh, she also has, uh...

14:38.711 --> 14:42.749
Lucky Charms
and Cinnamon Toast Crunch.

14:46.920 --> 14:48.855
[ Utensil clatters ]

14:48.888 --> 14:52.059
Why do you keep looking
at your laptop?

14:52.092 --> 14:53.293
I'm not.

14:53.326 --> 14:54.527
Is that porn?

14:54.561 --> 14:55.996
[ Scoffs ]

15:00.267 --> 15:02.269
What is this?

15:02.302 --> 15:04.037
Is this a book?
You're writing a book?

15:04.071 --> 15:06.739
It's a short story.
I'm taking a class.

15:09.276 --> 15:10.610
This is about me.

15:10.643 --> 15:12.579
What? No, it's not.
It's totally about me.

15:12.612 --> 15:14.647
"Her hands swept over
the display,

15:14.681 --> 15:17.650
"snatching up the emerald
earrings in one fluid motion,

15:17.684 --> 15:21.221
like an eagle snatching
a salmon."

15:21.254 --> 15:23.156
It's not a great metaphor.
Uhh...

15:23.190 --> 15:24.992
People don't want to
think about eagles

15:25.025 --> 15:26.226
when they're reading about me.

15:26.259 --> 15:27.961
It's a simile,
and it's not about you!

15:27.995 --> 15:30.930
"And that's when she found
the body, skin flayed,

15:30.964 --> 15:34.334
hanging from the ceiling
of the wine cellar."

15:34.367 --> 15:36.169
What is this?

15:36.203 --> 15:39.006
What's the matter with you?
It's a work in progress!

15:39.039 --> 15:41.574
Lisa Dobesh
is a very blah name.

15:41.608 --> 15:43.076
Just call her Letty.

15:43.110 --> 15:46.413
[ Cup clatters ]
Why are you here?

15:46.446 --> 15:49.649
Because I'm awesome, and I
make your life more awesome.

15:49.682 --> 15:52.685
Mm-hmm.
Why are you here?

15:52.719 --> 15:54.321
Where's Javier?

15:56.656 --> 16:00.793
[ Sighs ] Where's Jacob?

16:03.863 --> 16:07.167
[ Voice breaks ]
I took him back to my mom's.

16:07.200 --> 16:09.269
Oh, shit.

16:09.302 --> 16:10.803
[ Crying ]

16:10.837 --> 16:14.874
[ Footsteps circling ]

16:22.315 --> 16:24.317
[ Crying ]

16:24.351 --> 16:28.621
It's fine.
I'm better on my own.

16:28.655 --> 16:30.623
And, yet, here you are.

16:30.657 --> 16:33.393
[ Crying ]

16:33.426 --> 16:37.130
No, I -- I was just thinking
about how much fun we had

16:37.164 --> 16:39.566
when we robbed that hotel
together.

16:39.599 --> 16:41.368
We got caught by the FBI.

16:41.401 --> 16:44.003
I only got caught
because you got caught.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.972
I only got caught
because you convinced me

16:46.005 --> 16:48.241
to rob a hotel, so...

16:49.909 --> 16:51.378
I love you, Letty.

16:51.411 --> 16:52.645
Mm.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.147
I know.

16:54.181 --> 16:55.915
Because, yes, you do
bring awesomeness

16:55.948 --> 16:58.785
into people's lives,
but...

17:01.221 --> 17:05.892
If you're feeling, I don't know,
uh, lonely right now...

17:05.925 --> 17:09.362
maybe robbing a hotel with
your former parole officer

17:09.396 --> 17:12.332
shouldn't be plan "A."

17:12.365 --> 17:13.600
[ Sighs ]

17:13.633 --> 17:16.503
You used to be fun.
Marriage has changed you.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.771
Mm-hmm. You need friends.

17:18.805 --> 17:20.039
You're my friend.

17:20.073 --> 17:23.343
I know, but you need
more than one friend.

17:23.376 --> 17:26.279
Make another one!

17:26.313 --> 17:32.552
A non-user, non-hit man,
maybe only mildly crazy friend.

17:32.585 --> 17:35.288
Where? On Facebook?

17:35.322 --> 17:36.389
Maybe go somewhere

17:36.423 --> 17:39.426
where you might actually
make good decisions.

17:39.459 --> 17:42.095
Where you won't be so...

17:45.832 --> 17:48.801
Where's the last place
you felt safe?

17:48.835 --> 17:53.306
Maybe even settled
a little?

17:53.340 --> 17:57.076
That might be the right place
to make a friend.

18:02.749 --> 18:04.617
Congrats on the wedding.

18:04.651 --> 18:06.386
You got me a Mont Blanc pen?

18:06.419 --> 18:09.256
And I didn't even know you
were trying to be a writer.

18:11.258 --> 18:13.260
Thanks?

18:15.262 --> 18:17.997
But, seriously, you should
change her name to Letty.

18:18.030 --> 18:19.999
I'll think about it.

18:21.468 --> 18:25.472
And her handbag should be
a quilted leather Chanel.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.609
[ Door closes ]

18:33.012 --> 18:35.248
[ Typing ]

18:35.282 --> 18:37.250
**

18:37.284 --> 18:38.951
[ Horn honks in distance ]

18:38.985 --> 18:41.854
[ Cart clattering ]

18:41.888 --> 18:46.593
**

18:46.626 --> 18:50.197
[ Bag rustling ]

18:50.230 --> 18:54.934
**

18:54.967 --> 18:58.205
**

19:00.973 --> 19:03.042
[ Beep ]

19:12.652 --> 19:16.356
[ Sighs ]

19:19.158 --> 19:24.331
If you scream, I'll drive
my elbow into your esophagus.

19:28.435 --> 19:29.936
[ Groans ]

19:32.839 --> 19:34.507
[ Groans ]

19:37.344 --> 19:40.247
I'm not the screaming type.

19:40.280 --> 19:44.016
I forgot to hit the button
on the A/C.

19:45.752 --> 19:47.987
And then this crazy heat wave...

19:48.020 --> 19:51.524
Global fucking warming, huh?

19:51.558 --> 19:53.926
You must be thirsty.

19:59.532 --> 20:02.535
[ Liquid splashing ]

20:12.044 --> 20:15.081
[ Speaking Spanish ]

20:35.735 --> 20:37.937
[ Thud ]
[ Grunts ]

20:37.970 --> 20:40.407
[ Groans ]

20:44.611 --> 20:47.079
Why?

20:49.916 --> 20:52.419
Why did you kill Silk?

20:53.753 --> 20:56.088
His haircut.

20:57.590 --> 20:59.058
[ Thud ]

20:59.091 --> 21:00.960
[ Exhales ]

21:02.094 --> 21:04.964
Why did you try to kill me?

21:04.997 --> 21:09.402
You really haven't
figured it out yet?

21:09.436 --> 21:10.637
Hmm?

21:14.541 --> 21:16.509
Mm.

21:42.669 --> 21:44.971
[ Exhales sharply ]

21:45.004 --> 21:48.274
[ Muffled grunting ]

21:48.307 --> 21:50.777
[ Heavy breathing ]

21:50.810 --> 21:52.345
Woman's voice: Your call
has been forwarded

21:52.379 --> 21:54.313
to an automated
voice-messaging system.

21:54.347 --> 21:56.616
[ Beep ]
Call me back.

21:56.649 --> 21:58.518
I need to talk to you.

22:04.056 --> 22:06.926
[ Birds chirping ]

22:16.836 --> 22:17.904
[ Keys jingling ]

22:17.937 --> 22:22.509
[ Lock rattles, dog barking ]

22:24.877 --> 22:27.213
I told the owner
you disappeared.

22:28.681 --> 22:31.384
Carin.

22:31.418 --> 22:34.153
Hi.
Mary Catherine put
the listing back up,

22:34.186 --> 22:36.188
and it rented out
in no time.

22:38.257 --> 22:41.060
I went out on a limb for you.
Way out.

22:41.093 --> 22:42.595
I got Michael that interview
at Cedarwood,

22:42.629 --> 22:44.731
and then, poof,
he disappeared.

22:44.764 --> 22:47.734
I'm sorry.

22:47.767 --> 22:49.536
Christmas got complicated.

22:49.569 --> 22:52.705
Okay, and you couldn't have
called?

22:52.739 --> 22:55.074
Or texted me back?

22:55.107 --> 22:57.276
I mean, we were friends.

22:57.309 --> 22:59.412
At least, I thought we were.

23:00.580 --> 23:01.948
I'm sorry, Carin.

23:01.981 --> 23:03.783
Mary Catherine wanted to sell
all of your stuff on Craigslist,

23:03.816 --> 23:06.986
but I put it in my garage
because I am a good friend.

23:08.788 --> 23:10.723
You're right. I'm sorry.

23:10.757 --> 23:14.026
But we went on this trip
with my mom, and...

23:14.060 --> 23:16.663
everything got out of hand.

23:17.930 --> 23:19.331
Emile?

23:20.767 --> 23:22.735
Yeah.

23:22.769 --> 23:24.471
Did he cheat on you?

23:27.306 --> 23:29.709
Yeah.

23:29.742 --> 23:33.446
Oh, my God.
I am so sorry, honey.

23:33.480 --> 23:35.815
Right.

23:35.848 --> 23:38.585
Should've seen it coming.

23:38.618 --> 23:42.088
I knew he was bad
from day one.

