42:31.883 --> 42:33.719
but I'm a shitty mom

42:33.752 --> 42:37.656
who...probably shouldn't
even have custody.

42:39.625 --> 42:44.029
My son is with my mom now,

42:44.062 --> 42:48.967
and that's probably where
he should stay until he's 18.

42:54.005 --> 42:58.543
And Javier --
that's his real name --

42:58.576 --> 43:01.713
he didn't cheat on me.

43:01.747 --> 43:04.482
We're just no good together.

43:12.157 --> 43:16.895
I suck at a lot of things people
are supposed to be good at.

43:16.928 --> 43:19.397
But I'm pretty great
at a lot of things

43:19.430 --> 43:22.533
you're not supposed
to be good at.

43:23.635 --> 43:26.672
I was wondering a little.

43:26.705 --> 43:31.142
Especially after the watch.

43:31.176 --> 43:33.812
Yeah.

43:33.845 --> 43:36.982
A move like that is pretty
typical for me.

43:38.850 --> 43:41.619
I guess I thought
I could fake being a mom

43:41.653 --> 43:44.723
like I fake everything else.

43:46.858 --> 43:49.761
Last year,

43:49.795 --> 43:51.763
Apple's principal called

43:51.797 --> 43:55.133
because they caught her trying
to start a fire in the bathroom.

43:55.166 --> 44:00.005
So, I got in my car,
and I drove to the school,

44:00.038 --> 44:03.508
and then I drove
right past it.

44:03.541 --> 44:07.979
I drove all the way
to Savannah.

44:08.013 --> 44:10.682
Got a bourbon

44:10.716 --> 44:12.650
and a toffee pudding,

44:12.684 --> 44:15.854
and I had them while
I sat on the beach.

44:15.887 --> 44:18.156
And then...

44:18.189 --> 44:22.193
it eventually got dark,
and I drove back.

44:22.227 --> 44:24.730
What happened to Apple?

44:24.763 --> 44:27.833
Oh, Eric spoke
to the principal

44:27.866 --> 44:31.569
and...donated...
[ Sighs ]

44:31.602 --> 44:34.572
a volleyball net
or something,

44:34.605 --> 44:37.542
and he never
mentioned it again.

44:39.677 --> 44:41.412
Being a person isn't easy,

44:41.446 --> 44:47.185
but being a mother
and a person --

44:47.218 --> 44:50.621
that's fuckin' hard.

44:57.428 --> 44:59.597
We need more coke.

45:01.199 --> 45:03.201
[ Laughs ]

45:04.702 --> 45:07.438
I saw a dealer
near that nightclub.

45:07.472 --> 45:09.908
Are you serious?

45:09.941 --> 45:12.744
Oh, I can't even
stand up right now.

45:12.778 --> 45:14.913
All I want to do
is go to sleep.

45:14.946 --> 45:17.348
You just said this was
the most fun you've ever had.

45:17.382 --> 45:20.418
Yeah, but now it's over.

45:20.451 --> 45:22.854
[ Huffs ]

45:22.888 --> 45:26.391
You can sleep in the guest room
if you want.

45:26.424 --> 45:29.127
Thanks. I'll do that.

45:31.162 --> 45:33.464
Don't forget all your stuff
in the garage.

45:33.498 --> 45:36.101
Uh-huh. Whatever.

45:36.134 --> 45:40.138
**

45:40.171 --> 45:42.808
[ Clattering ]

45:50.281 --> 45:51.716
[ Rustling ]

45:51.749 --> 45:54.419
[ Dog barking in distance ]

45:54.452 --> 45:55.787
[ Rustling continues ]

45:55.821 --> 45:57.688
[ Door closes ]

46:04.595 --> 46:06.832
Carlos.

46:09.667 --> 46:11.837
[ Speaking Spanish ]

46:26.017 --> 46:29.320
**

46:56.647 --> 47:00.685
**

47:10.261 --> 47:16.234
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

47:20.738 --> 47:23.041
I knew you couldn't go
too long without me.

47:23.074 --> 47:26.511
Your humility
is unparalleled.

47:26.544 --> 47:27.979
Thanks.

47:28.013 --> 47:30.315
Yeah, I've been thinking
about you.

47:30.348 --> 47:33.218
A-About what you said
the other day.

47:33.251 --> 47:35.553
I can't get it
out of my head.

47:35.586 --> 47:37.422
Yeah?
Yeah.

47:37.455 --> 47:40.391
I mean, when I finally
took a step back,

47:40.425 --> 47:43.194
looked at the situation,
it all became clear.

47:43.228 --> 47:46.364
My main character is
completely based on you.

47:46.397 --> 47:48.233
I don't know why
I couldn't see it.

47:48.266 --> 47:50.668
I must've had some kind of
mental block.

47:50.701 --> 47:52.437
You're calling me about
your short story?

47:52.470 --> 47:54.072
[ Voice fading ]
You said she should have

47:54.105 --> 47:56.407
a quilted leather Chanel bag.

47:56.441 --> 47:59.777
Now, what other kind of
details would you add?

48:02.780 --> 48:06.184
[ "Let it Down" by Edward Sharpe
and the Magnetic Zeroes plays ]

48:06.217 --> 48:15.726
**

48:15.760 --> 48:19.230
* The dawn

48:19.264 --> 48:22.400
* Fixed behind a curtain

48:22.433 --> 48:27.438
* Two fingers of satin

48:27.472 --> 48:31.943
* Spun in the moonlight

48:31.977 --> 48:36.814
* Playing the air

48:36.847 --> 48:40.818
* No home

48:40.851 --> 48:45.090
* Spinning

48:45.123 --> 48:48.960
* In the sunlight

48:48.994 --> 48:53.731
* Remember us laughing

48:53.764 --> 48:58.669
* On acid

48:58.703 --> 49:02.640
* Let it down

49:02.673 --> 49:05.143
* Let it heal from memories

49:05.176 --> 49:08.179
You, me, and Chrissy
makes three.

49:08.213 --> 49:13.318
* 'Member you, 'member me,
'member love, memories *

49:13.351 --> 49:16.487
* Memories

49:16.521 --> 49:19.857
* Doo-da-da-da-eh

49:21.326 --> 49:31.302
**

49:31.336 --> 49:41.312
**

49:41.346 --> 49:48.753
**
